Polish Stocks: GTC, PGNiG, Lotos, PKN Orlen Move in Warsaw

-- B y   P a w e l   K o z l o w s k i   a n d   M a r e k   S t r z e l e c k i
-- 
2011-07-21T16:35:30Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-21/polish-stocks-cez-pbg-bank-pekao-telekomunikacja-move.html
Poland ’s WIG20 Index rose 36.29
points, or 1.4 percent, to 2,729.46 at the 5:30 p.m. close in
Warsaw.  The following are among the most active stocks on the
 Warsaw Stock Exchange  today. Stock symbols follow company names.  Globe Trade Centre SA (GTC)  , Poland’s largest property
developer by market value, jumped 0.86 zloty, or 5.5 percent to
16.64 zloty. GTC was raised to “hold from ‘‘sell’’ at Deutsche
Bank AG.  Polskie Gornictwo Naftowe i Gazownictwo SA (PGN)  ,
Poland’s biggest natural-gas company, rose 0.18 zloty, or 4.2
percent to 4.44 zloty. The company signed a deal with banks to
increase its domestic bond program to 5 billion zloty ($1.8
billion) from 3 billion zloty to help finance investments.  PKN Orlen SA (PKN PW), Poland’s biggest oil company, rose
0.7 zloty, or 1.6 percent, to 45.7 zloty.  Grupa Lotos SA (LTS)  , the second-largest refiner, jumped 1.75 zloty, or 4.7
percent, to 39.4 zloty. Crude oil increased on reports European
Union officials have come up with a plan for the region’s debt
crisis, bolstering the euro.  To contact the reporter on this story:
